        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 7:27PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 727 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 5 miles
northwest of Soper, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.

Locations in or near the path include...
Ord...                            Grant...
Kent...                           Soper...
Boswell...                        Rattan...
Fallon...                         Goodland...
Messer...                         Darwin...
Apple...                          Speer...
Dela...                           Hugo...
Kellond...                        Unger...
Antlers...                        Gay...
Arthur City...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
